4.  Look for files created or changed within ±30 minutes of 2008-07-20 01:28:03  timestamp.
Create two time reference files:
$ touch before -t 200807200058              # 12:58 AM
$ touch after -t 200807200158                 # 01:58 PM
Then run:
$ find ./ -newer before ! -newer after -type f -exec stat --format '%n %s %A %U %G %y %x %z %w' {} \; > /Path-To/Files-Modified-1hWindow
You’ll get just the files modified in that 1-hour window
		Flag        Meaning
%n        File name
%s        File size in bytes
%A        File permissions
%U        File owner name
%G        File group name
%y        Modification time
%x        Access time
%z        Change time
%w        Birth time (if supported)
