6. Detect Obfuscates Sttrings (N'e.w".o'B'j.e'C'T)
$ grep -Ei "([A-Za-z](['\"\.-]+)?){3,}"
([A-Za-z](['\".\.-]+)?){3,}
• [A-Za-z] → matches a letter.
• (['\"\.-]+)? → optionally followed by ', ", ., or -.
• ? = “zero or one occurrence” of the preceding element. Example: colou?r --> Matches: color or colour (? apply to u)
• + = Match one or more of the preceding element. Example: [0-9]+ → matches any integer (one or more digits).
• {3,} → repeat at least 3 times (so it catches obfuscated words like N'e.w".o'B'j.e'C'T).

