$ nc -vz 10.10.14.23 31337
nc → netcat, a tool to make raw network connections.
-v → verbose, tells you what’s happening.
-z → zero-I/O mode, don’t actually send data, just check if the port is open (like a port scanner).
10.10.14.23 → the target host (your Sliver server box).
31337 → the target port (the Sliver server mTLS listener).
$ ss -tulpn | grep 31337
ss → “socket statistics.” A modern replacement for netstat, shows all sockets and listening ports.
-t → show TCP sockets.
-u → show UDP sockets.
-l → show only listening sockets.
-p → show the process that owns the socket.
-n → show numeric addresses/ports (don’t resolve service names like http).
| grep 31337 → filter the results to only show entries with port 31337.
